<p>Start with 10 to 15 long-tail keywords. Write one post per keyword. Track rankings weekly in Google Search Console. The first page-1 ranking usually arrives within 60 days for keywords under KD 20.</p>
<p><strong>Impact timeline:</strong> 30 to 90 days for low-KD keywords to reach page 1.</p>
<h2>Strategy 2: Build Content Clusters Around Pillar Pages</h2>
<p>Isolated blog posts on random topics do not build authority. Content clusters do.</p>
<p>A <a href="/blog/what-is-content-cluster/">content cluster</a> is a group of 8 to 15 related blog posts organized around a central <a href="/blog/write-pillar-page/">pillar page</a>. The pillar covers the broad topic. Cluster pages cover subtopics in depth. Internal links connect everything.</p>
<p>Sites with topic clusters drive 30 to 43% more organic traffic than sites with unconnected content.</p>
<p><strong>How to build a cluster:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Choose a broad topic your business is an authority on.</li>
<li>Map 8 to 15 subtopics, each targeting a unique keyword.</li>
<li>Write the pillar page (3,000 to 5,000 words covering every subtopic at a high level).</li>
<li>Write cluster pages (1,500 to 3,500 words each on specific subtopics).</li>
<li>Link every cluster page to the pillar. Link the pillar to every cluster page.</li>
</ul>
<p>Read our guide on <a href="/blog/build-topical-authority/">building topical authority</a> for the complete cluster strategy.</p>
<p><strong>Impact timeline:</strong> 3 to 6 months for the cluster compounding effect to become visible.</p>
