<h2>Strategy 6: Build Strategic Internal Links</h2>
<p>Internal links distribute page authority across your site. They help Google discover new pages. They keep readers engaged longer. Sites with strong internal linking rank faster for new content.</p>
<p><strong>Internal linking rules:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>3 to 5 internal links per 1,000 words.</li>
<li>Use descriptive anchor text (not "click here").</li>
<li>Link to topically related pages.</li>
<li>Distribute links across sections. Do not cluster in one paragraph.</li>
<li>Update old posts to link to new content (most teams skip this step).</li>
</ul>
<p>Read our guide on <a href="/blog/internal-linking-blog-posts/">internal linking for blog posts</a> for the full strategy.</p>
<p><strong>Impact timeline:</strong> 2 to 4 weeks. Internal link changes propagate as Google re-crawls linked pages.</p>
<h2>Strategy 7: Earn Backlinks Through Link-Worthy Content</h2>
<p>Backlinks remain one of the top 3 ranking factors. The number 1 result on Google has 3.8 times more backlinks than results in positions 2 through 10.</p>
<p>Not all content earns links. The content types that attract the most backlinks are:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Data studies and original research.</strong> Sites link to your data as a source.</li>
<li><strong>Ultimate guides and definitive resources.</strong> Other writers reference your guide.</li>
<li><strong>Free tools and calculators.</strong> Utility content earns links naturally.</li>
<li><strong>Infographics and visual data.</strong> Easy to embed and credit.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Practical link building actions:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Publish original data or research in your niche.</li>
<li>Create a free tool related to your industry. See our <a href="/tools/seo-audit/">free SEO tools</a> for examples.</li>
<li>Write guest posts on industry blogs with a link back to your pillar content.</li>
<li>Fix broken links on other sites by offering your content as a replacement.</li>
</ol>
<p>Read our guide on <a href="/blog/build-backlinks-for-blog/">building backlinks for your blog</a> for 10+ link building tactics.</p>
<p><strong>Impact timeline:</strong> 1 to 3 months. Backlinks take time to accrue authority.</p>
<h2>Strategy 8: Match Content Format to Search Intent</h2>
<p>Google ranks pages that match <a href="/blog/search-intent-guide/">search intent</a>. Write the wrong format for the intent and your page will not rank, regardless of word count or backlinks.</p>
<p><strong>The 4 types of search intent:</strong></p>
<div class="table-wrap"><table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Intent</th>
<th>Signal</th>
<th>Best Format</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
