<h2>Strategy 11: Run Quarterly Content Audits</h2>
<p>A content audit identifies underperforming pages that drag down your site's average quality. It also surfaces opportunities to consolidate, redirect, or update content for maximum impact.</p>
<p><strong>What to audit every 90 days:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Pages with zero organic traffic (consider consolidating or removing).</li>
<li>Pages ranking on page 2 (push to page 1 with updates and internal links).</li>
<li>Pages with high impressions but low CTR (improve titles and descriptions).</li>
<li>Duplicate or near-duplicate content (consolidate into one strong page).</li>
<li>Pages with outdated information (refresh with current data).</li>
</ul>
<p>Read our guide on <a href="/blog/how-to-content-audit/">how to do a content audit</a> for the full process.</p>
<p><strong>Impact timeline:</strong> 30 to 60 days after implementing audit recommendations.</p>
